reviews.title: Top restaurant
reviews.text: After a long time somewhere had a complete evening. It started with the menu is extensive and super tasty dishes. The service was real hospitality where also the chef himself went along the tables to see if everything was satisfactory. Here we will enjoy more often💪🏻

reviews.title: Too many minuses.
reviews.text:
We have been here for lunch
I myself had an omelette with salmon that tasted even though the bread (the crust) was quite chewy.
My partner had a salad grilled chicken with cashews with ras el hanout sauce.
Bah: the chicken was limp and not grilled and not seasoned. 
No cashews and the salad was just some leaves of lettuce really soaked in very sour dressing. You can't eat that.
Reported this to the waitress who did not reconsider. When I reported it on payment she said it would be discussed in the next meeting. Bullshit.

reviews.title: Top service and fantastic flavor combinations
reviews.text:
Had a fantastic, delicious surprise menu. Where our preferences were taken into account. Good service, as it should be!
A truly wonderful evening out and a long meal.

reviews.title: Roast-it is also a good choice for lunch
reviews.text: Had a delicious lunch at Roast-It. Plenty of choice, delicious dishes and good wine. Roast it is the place if you like good BBQ dishes. But in addition to dining, you can also have a very good lunch there. I'll come more often!

reviews.title: Lunch without pleasure!
reviews.text: That was another catering experience that deprives you of the pleasure of going again. What immediately caused irritation was the music that was at the level of electronic garbage with an irritating heavy bass and the sound level was much too loud, the waiter did not respond to my reaction. Service is friendly, we ordered a "glass" of white dry wine and indeed a glass with a capacity of around 100cc (7 from the bottle) came with the "reasonable" price of 5.50 euros! How does a catering entrepreneur evict the customer? My other half had a Carpaccio sandwich as it should be (10.95), I myself had a Hanoi pork belly sandwich in oyster sauce, unfortunately you had to look for the bacon, not enough 4/5 pieces, the sauce had turned the bread into porridge, The attachments were fine but at the price 15.95 euros. Lunch came to 47.90. What was also striking was that the salt and pepper set consisted of a pepper mill and a container containing the salt that you had to remove with your fingers! I think the NVWA has an opinion about that. Furthermore, the place could use a makeover, the floor doesn't look good, the chairs are full of stains and the tables could use some sanding and re-lacquering. Not recommended unfortunately, it is what it is.

reviews.title: An addition to the Borne restaurant scene
reviews.text:
We arrived with a reservation this time, and one person has a severe gluten allergy which I  wrote to the restaurant when making the reservation on line which was easy to do.

The kind and friendly waitress spoke English which was helpful due to my American friend who was eating with us<;
We ordered sparkling water and then we ordered the dishes.

One thing about the way too many pages of the menu. very confusing and definetely not Menu Design 101. A menu shoud have a front cover, then 2 inside pages and a back page but alas this was not the case.

I ordered a sandwich with brown, delicious fresh bread with goat cheese and my American friend ordered a Vitello tonato (and I took leftover home). and my mother ordered a Glutenfree dish with goat cheese - a sort of crème brûlée - with GF bread.

The latter was too greasy - too much butter was used in the pan to heat up the bread and my mother got really sick eating this  - 24 hours later.

The dessert - a cheesecake one - was fluffy and very good.

The bill came to aprox; 70 euros for 3.

reviews.title: Best place in Borne for roasts
reviews.text: I had an excellent short rib, but also the spare ribs and carpaccio were very good. Nice selection of starters, and good wine.

reviews.title: good food
reviews.text:
nice restaurant in the centre of Borne, cozy terras, good interior.
Food was great, freindly staff. portians are big, so watch what your ordering.

reviews.title: Very very Nice!
reviews.text: First time around and enjoyed a very good sandwich! Great ambiance. Good staff. Fast service. Will definitely go back when I am back in town!

When you only have 48 hours to get to know Dubai, deciding what makes it onto your must-see list might feel impossible. But I love a challenge, which is why I thought back on all the time I’ve spent here over the years and crafted a two-day itinerary that crams in all of the essentials. You’ll hit all the high points—starting with the observation deck at the Burj Khalifa, the world’s tallest building—as well as shopping malls the size of small cities and  islands that didn’t even exist a few years ago.

articleContent.title: 5 perfect days in New York City

seoInfo.metaDescription: More than 60 million people visit New York City every year, and a huge percentage of them only hit the big sites—Times Square, the Empire State Building, etc. I get it: They’re iconic. But as someone who has lived in this city for more than 30 years, I’m here to tell you that you’re missing out if you don’t mix in some off-the-beaten path locations. Luckily, five days gives you plenty of time to do just that.

articleContent.title: Celebrate the best of Osaka’s food and nightlife with Suntory

seoInfo.metaDescription: If you’ve ever found yourself standing in line for hours at a famous ramen spot in Japan, you’d probably agree that food and drinks are a big part of why we travel. It’s one of the best ways to get a glimpse into a destination's culture, traditions, and history, whether it’s through its local dishes, ingredients, or culinary customs. But if you really want to embrace local culture, there’s no better way than over a glass. Share a drink with locals, friends, and fellow travelers, and experience the camaraderie, stories, and traditions that make up the heart of a destination, forging deeper connections along the way.
